their own ſinfulneſs, and Chriſts righteouſneſs; their own wants, and Chriſts fulneſs; their own guilt, and Chriſts ſatisfaction: The miſery of their eſtate, as the children of the firſt Adam; and the happineſs of their eſtate▪ by virtue of union with the Lord Chriſt the ſecond Adam, Joh. 16. 8, 9, 10, 11. 1 Cor. 2 9. to the end, Eph. 1. 16, 17, 18, 19, 20. Be faithfull in the making uſe of theſe directions, and by the bleſſing of the Lord upon thee, thou mayeſt come to know the ſtate of thy ſoul, whether thou art in the broad way to deſtruction, or in the narrow ſtreight path to life and glory.
